post_text:
After careful consideration and the monitoring of local and state agencies, Amite County School District will begin to implement a return to traditional schedule. It is in the best interest of our students and community that we proceed on this path. We will continue to use every safety precaution to ensure that all students and staff are protected.

Phase 1: On September 21, 2020 all students will return to a full school week (Mon-Fri).

Time will remain abbreviated at a 1:00 p.m. dismissal.

Phase 2: On October 5, 2020 all students will return to a traditional schedule (Mon-Fri).

Bus dismissal will begin 3:00 p.m. Elementary.

Bus dismissal will begin 3:15 p.m. High School.

post_text:
After much deliberation, district leaders and school board members have decided that postponing the start date of the 20-21 school year is in the best interest of our students, faculty, and community.

Keeping everyone healthy and safe is extremely important to us. With the ongoing threat of the COVID-19 virus, we think this is the best decision for everyone.

District leaders will begin working on an updated 20-21 school calendar this week. We will use September 8th, as our proposed start date. Once school board approved, the calendar will be posted on the district website as soon as possible.

We appreciate your continued support and understanding.

Mississippi State University in Starkville, MS will be having Spring Preview Days on February 17th and March 23rd.

MSU encourages students and parents to select the date that works best for their schedule. There is a $10 charge per person. Upon arrival, students will receive a packet of information and a t-shirt for their participation. Lunch will be provided along with some of their famous MSU ice cream.

Online registration goes live on January 17th at 9 a.m.

For more information, please visit SpringPreview.msstate.edu. If there are any questions, please feel free to contact MSU by email at events@msstate.edu.

Parents, Alumni, and stakeholders of the Amite County School District:

There will be a community stakeholder meeting held by the Mississippi School Board Association on May 2, at 5:30 p.m. at ACHS in the auditorium.

The meeting will last approximately 45 minutes to one hour. The goal of the meeting is to get input from stakeholders about the characteristics desired in the new superintendent and priorities which should be addressed by the new superintendent.

Input from the meetings will be scripted, and paper surveys will be distributed. The survey will also be available online beginning on May 3, 2019, for two weeks. Stakeholder input will be used to develop a brochure to advertise the position, to develop interview questions, and to use as a foundation for the board members in making their decision as to whom to hire.

Success Message for Families:
Children are more likely to be courteous and respectful if the practice is presented as a family rule and not just something that only they are required to do. “Remember, the Jones family always uses good manners,” is more likely to get an improved response than, “I want you to stop that.”

Message from ACSD Band Director, Claude Harness:

We are so excited about our new school year! Our initial Band Booster Meeting has been scheduled for 5:30 p.m. on Tuesday, August 21, 2018 in the band room at Amite County High School.

We are grateful for all our amazing parents and supporters for the assistance during our previous school year. Let's make this year the GREATEST year ever! We are encouraging all band parents, supporters as well as ACSD alumni to attend this meeting. We welcome your ideas and your positive input during this meeting. Our goal is to continue to move our band program to the next level of excellence. With your support, we know that we can achieve our goal.

As always, we appreciate your support and thank you for making this date a priority on your calendar.

Respectfully yours, Mr. Claude A. Harness Band Director, ACSD

We are encouraging all band parents, supporters as well as ACSD alumni to attend this meeting. We welcome your ideas and your positive input during this meeting. Our goal is to continue to move our band program to the next level of excellence. With your support, we know that we can achieve our goal.

As always, we appreciate your support and thank you for making this date a priority on your calendar.

Respectfully yours, Mr. Claude A. Harness Band Director, ACSD

WHAT PARENTS NEED TO KNOW ABOUT TITLE I
May 22, 10:30 a.m. at the School Board Office

We value Family Engagement at our school and all staff believe that effectively engaging families is critical for every child’s success.
PURPOSE: You are invited to participate in a meeting to help develop Family Engagement programs and Activities that will be implemented for the upcoming school year. Help us to go “above and beyond” as we develop activities, workshops and events to help all parents at our schools to be full partners in the education of our children. The input from this meeting will be used to develop and update our School Parent and Family Engagement Policy.

AGENDA
Family Engagement Policy Review
Parent Compact
Parent Survey
School Parent and Family Engagement Policy-Review/Revise Family Involvement Workshop

Refreshments will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you at the meeting!

Parents can also take the following online survey here:
https://goo.gl/forms/eSq1axjqj6GZM2982

post_text:
ACHS Beta Club is putting on Amite County's 1st annual "Amite County's Got Talent" on May 4th at 6:30 p.m. in the ACHS auditorium. We will be showcasing several talents from around the school and also a few special acts for your enjoyment. We would like to invite everyone to attend. Tickets for the show are $5 in advance and $6 at the door. There will be concessions and plenty of song, dance and fun.

Come support your students, classmates, friends, family and school. Show us that Trojan Spirit!!!

Tickets can be purchased from any Beta club member, Mrs. Weathers, Mrs. Watts or Mr. Bui.

Student artwork will be also be displayed in the halls.
Come join the fun!!
